title: 2014–15 Svenska Cupen Qualifying Rounds
text:
The 2014–15 Svenska Cupen is the 59th season of <a href="Svenska%20Cupen">Svenska Cupen</a> and the third season with the current format. The winners of the competition will earn a place in the <a href="2015%E2%80%9316%20UEFA%20Europa%20League%23Second%20qualifying%20round">second qualifying round</a> of the <a href="2015%E2%80%9316%20UEFA%20Europa%20League">2015–16 UEFA Europa League</a>, unless they have already qualified for European competition, in which case the qualification spot will go to another team, determined by a <a href="2014%E2%80%9315%20Svenska%20Cupen%23European%20competition%20qualification">number of factors</a>.
A total of 96 clubs will enter the competition. <a href="IF%20Elfsborg">IF Elfsborg</a> are the <a href="2013%E2%80%9314%20Svenska%20Cupen">defending champions</a>, having beaten <a href="Helsingborgs%20IF">Helsingborgs IF</a> 1–0 in <a href="2014%20Svenska%20Cupen%20Final">last season's final</a>.
The only two associations of the <a href="Swedish%20District%20Football%20Associations">Swedish District Football Associations</a> that had a qualifying tournament were <a href="Dalarnas%20Fotbollf%C3%B6rbund">Dalarnas FF</a> and <a href="%C3%96rebro%20L%C3%A4ns%20Fotbollf%C3%B6rbund">Örebro Läns FF</a>, the other districts decided their teams by "Distriktsmästerskap" (District Championships) or by club ranking 2013.
Dalarnas FF qualification.
The first round commenced on 13 March 2014 and the final was contested on 28 May 2014. The five highest ranked teams entered teams entered in the quarter-finals. The number in brackets, indicate what tier of <a href="Sweden">Swedish</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> each team competed in for the <a href="2014%20in%20Swedish%20football">2014</a> season.
Örebro Läns FF qualification.
The first match was played on 5 March 2014 and the last match was played on 13 May 2014. The number in brackets, indicate what tier of <a href="Sweden">Swedish</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> each team competed in for the <a href="2014%20in%20Swedish%20football">2014</a> season.
Final round.
The winners of the final round entered the first round of <a href="2014%E2%80%9315%20Svenska%20Cupen">2014–15 Svenska Cupen</a>.
